com.idevicesinc.sweetblue

Enum BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status>
      • com.idevicesinc.sweetblue.BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    UsesCustomNull, Serializable, Comparable<BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status>
    Enclosing interface:
    BleDevice.ReadWriteListener

    public static enum BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status
extends Enum<BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status>
implements UsesCustomNull
    A value returned to BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.onEvent(ReadWriteEvent) by way of BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.status() that indicates success of the operation or the reason for its failure. This enum is not meant to match up with BluetoothGatt.GATT_* values in any way.
    See Also:
    BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.status()

      ANDROID_VERSION_NOT_SUPPORTED
      The android api level doesn't support the lower level API call in the native stack.
      CANCELLED_FROM_BLE_TURNING_OFF
      The operation was cancelled because BleManager went BleManagerState.TURNING_OFF and/or BleManagerState.OFF.
      CANCELLED_FROM_DISCONNECT
      The operation was cancelled by the device becoming BleDeviceState.DISCONNECTED.
      EMPTY_DATA
      Used either when BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.type() BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Type.isRead() and the operation was "successful" but returned a zero-length array for BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.data(), or BleDevice.write(UUID, byte[]) (or overload(s) ) was called with a non-null but zero-length data parameter.
      FAILED_TO_SEND_OUT
      The call to BluetoothGatt.readCharacteristic(BluetoothGattCharacteristic) or BluetoothGatt.writeCharacteristic(BluetoothGattCharacteristic) or etc.

      BluetoothGattCharacteristic.setValue(byte[]) (or one of its overloads) or BluetoothGattDescriptor.setValue(byte[]) (or one of its overloads) returned false.

      NOT_CONNECTED
      Device is not BleDeviceState.CONNECTED.
      NULL
      As of now, only used for BleDevice.ConnectionFailListener.ConnectionFailEvent.txnFailReason() in some cases.
      NULL_DATA
      Used either when BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.type() BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Type.isRead() and the stack returned a null value for BluetoothGattCharacteristic.getValue() despite the operation being otherwise "successful", or BleDevice.write(UUID, byte[]) (or overload(s) ) were called with a null data parameter.
      NULL_DEVICE
      BleDevice.read(UUID, ReadWriteListener), BleDevice.write(UUID, byte[]), BleDevice.enableNotify(UUID, ReadWriteListener), etc.
      OPERATION_NOT_SUPPORTED
      You tried to do a read on a characteristic that is write-only, or vice-versa, or tried to read a notify-only characteristic, or etc., etc.

      Specific to BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Target.RELIABLE_WRITE, this means BleDevice.reliableWrite_abort() was called.
      RELIABLE_WRITE_ALREADY_BEGAN
      Specific to BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Target.RELIABLE_WRITE, this means BleDevice.reliableWrite_begin(ReadWriteListener) was called twice without an intervening call to either BleDevice.reliableWrite_abort() or BleDevice.reliableWrite_execute().
      RELIABLE_WRITE_FAILED_TO_BEGIN

      SUCCESS

      Operation took longer than time specified in BleNodeConfig.taskTimeoutRequestFilter so we cut it loose.

      • SUCCESS

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status SUCCESS
        If BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.type() BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Type.isRead() then BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.data() will contain some data returned from the device. If type is BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Type.WRITE then BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.data() was sent to the device.

      • NULL_DEVICE

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status NULL_DEVICE
        BleDevice.read(UUID, ReadWriteListener), BleDevice.write(UUID, byte[]), BleDevice.enableNotify(UUID, ReadWriteListener), etc. was called on BleDevice.NULL.

      • NOT_CONNECTED

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status NOT_CONNECTED
        Device is not BleDeviceState.CONNECTED.

      • NO_MATCHING_TARGET

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status NO_MATCHING_TARGET
        Couldn't find a matching BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.target() for the BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.charUuid() (or BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.descUuid() if BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.target() is BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Target.DESCRIPTOR) which was given to BleDevice.read(UUID, ReadWriteListener), BleDevice.write(UUID, byte[]), etc. This most likely means that the internal call to BluetoothGatt.discoverServices() didn't find any BluetoothGattService that contained a BluetoothGattCharacteristic for BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.charUuid().

      • RELIABLE_WRITE_FAILED_TO_BEGIN

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status RELIABLE_WRITE_FAILED_TO_BEGIN
        Specific to BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Target.RELIABLE_WRITE, this means the underlying call to BluetoothGatt.beginReliableWrite() returned false.

      • RELIABLE_WRITE_ALREADY_BEGAN

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status RELIABLE_WRITE_ALREADY_BEGAN
        Specific to BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Target.RELIABLE_WRITE, this means BleDevice.reliableWrite_begin(ReadWriteListener) was called twice without an intervening call to either BleDevice.reliableWrite_abort() or BleDevice.reliableWrite_execute().

      • RELIABLE_WRITE_NEVER_BEGAN

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status RELIABLE_WRITE_NEVER_BEGAN
        Specific to BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Target.RELIABLE_WRITE, this means BleDevice.reliableWrite_abort() or BleDevice.reliableWrite_execute() was called without a previous call to BleDevice.reliableWrite_begin(ReadWriteListener).

      • RELIABLE_WRITE_ABORTED

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status RELIABLE_WRITE_ABORTED
        Specific to BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Target.RELIABLE_WRITE, this means BleDevice.reliableWrite_abort() was called.

      • OPERATION_NOT_SUPPORTED

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status OPERATION_NOT_SUPPORTED
        You tried to do a read on a characteristic that is write-only, or vice-versa, or tried to read a notify-only characteristic, or etc., etc.

      • ANDROID_VERSION_NOT_SUPPORTED

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status ANDROID_VERSION_NOT_SUPPORTED
        The android api level doesn't support the lower level API call in the native stack. For example if you try to use BleDevice.setMtu(int, ReadWriteListener), which requires API level 21, and you are at level 18.

      • FAILED_TO_TOGGLE_NOTIFICATION

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status FAILED_TO_TOGGLE_NOTIFICATION
        BluetoothGatt.setCharacteristicNotification(BluetoothGattCharacteristic, boolean) returned false for an unknown reason. This BleDevice.ConnectionFailListener.Status is only relevant for calls to BleDevice.enableNotify(UUID, ReadWriteListener) and BleDevice.disableNotify(UUID, ReadWriteListener) (or the various overloads).

      • FAILED_TO_SET_VALUE_ON_TARGET

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status FAILED_TO_SET_VALUE_ON_TARGET
        BluetoothGattCharacteristic.setValue(byte[]) (or one of its overloads) or BluetoothGattDescriptor.setValue(byte[]) (or one of its overloads) returned false.

      • FAILED_TO_SEND_OUT

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status FAILED_TO_SEND_OUT
        The call to BluetoothGatt.readCharacteristic(BluetoothGattCharacteristic) or BluetoothGatt.writeCharacteristic(BluetoothGattCharacteristic) or etc. returned false and thus failed immediately for unknown reasons. No good remedy for this...perhaps try BleManager.reset().

      • CANCELLED_FROM_DISCONNECT

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status CANCELLED_FROM_DISCONNECT
        The operation was cancelled by the device becoming BleDeviceState.DISCONNECTED.

      • CANCELLED_FROM_BLE_TURNING_OFF

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status CANCELLED_FROM_BLE_TURNING_OFF
        The operation was cancelled because BleManager went BleManagerState.TURNING_OFF and/or BleManagerState.OFF. Note that if the user turns off BLE from their OS settings (airplane mode, etc.) then BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.status() could potentially be CANCELLED_FROM_DISCONNECT because SweetBlue might get the disconnect callback before the turning off callback. Basic testing has revealed that this is *not* the case, but you never know.

        Either way, the device was or will be disconnected.

      • NULL_DATA

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status NULL_DATA
        Used either when BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.type() BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Type.isRead() and the stack returned a null value for BluetoothGattCharacteristic.getValue() despite the operation being otherwise "successful", or BleDevice.write(UUID, byte[]) (or overload(s) ) were called with a null data parameter. For the read case, the library will throw an BleManager.UhOhListener.UhOh.READ_RETURNED_NULL, but hopefully it was just a temporary glitch. If the problem persists try BleManager.reset().

      • EMPTY_DATA

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status EMPTY_DATA
        Used either when BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.type() BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Type.isRead() and the operation was "successful" but returned a zero-length array for BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.data(), or BleDevice.write(UUID, byte[]) (or overload(s) ) was called with a non-null but zero-length data parameter. Note that BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.data() will be a zero-length array for all other error statuses as well, for example NO_MATCHING_TARGET, NOT_CONNECTED, etc. In other words it's never null.

      • INVALID_DATA

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status INVALID_DATA
        For now only used when giving a negative or zero value to BleDevice.setMtu(int, ReadWriteListener).

      • REMOTE_GATT_FAILURE

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status REMOTE_GATT_FAILURE
        The operation failed in a "normal" fashion, at least relative to all the other strange ways an operation can fail. This means for example that BluetoothGattCallback.onCharacteristicRead(BluetoothGatt, BluetoothGattCharacteristic, int) returned a status code that was not zero. This could mean the device went out of range, was turned off, signal was disrupted, whatever. Often this means that the device is about to become BleDeviceState.DISCONNECTED. BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.gattStatus() will most likely be non-zero, and you can check the static fields in BleStatuses for more information.
        See Also:
        BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent.gattStatus()

      • TIMED_OUT

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status TIMED_OUT
        Operation took longer than time specified in BleNodeConfig.taskTimeoutRequestFilter so we cut it loose.
